# PDF Comparison Tool 

A simple and powerful PDF comparison tool built with Python and Streamlit. It uses OCR to extract text from two PDFs and highlights word-level differences in a side-by-side view.

## Features
- Side-by-side PDF text comparison
- Word-level diff with highlights:
  - Green: added words
  - Red: removed words
- OCR support for scanned documents using `pytesseract`
- Scroll sync toggle for better navigation

## How to Run

1. Clone the repo:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/pdf-comparator.git
   cd pdf-comparator
